Copy the following code into VS 17.8.0 Preview 2:

```
using System.Runtime.CompilerServices;
using System.Security.Cryptography;
public struct Repro
{
	public ByteArray20 Data;
	public ByteArray20 Hash;

public void RecalculateHash()
	{
		SHA1. HashData(Data, Hash);
	}

[InlineArray(20)]
	public struct ByteArray20
	{
		private byte _byte;
	}
}
```

VS suggests `IDE0251 Member can be made 'readonly'` for the `RecalculateHash` method. Which is incorrect. If I accept the suggestion (adding `readonly` to `RecalculateHash`), the code correctly fails to compile with CS9164; the `Hash` member can't be treated as a (non-readonly) `Span<byte>`.

